records.addlTxt:
Defendant Corey D Conner in court with attorney Kevin B. Dunn.  James W. Frisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to each other.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.
Conditions:  
*  Successfully complete a course in anger management;
*  Possess no firearms;
*  No contact with Gregory M.;
*  Letter of apology to Gregory M.;
*  Serve 30 DAYS in the House of Correction consecutive to each other with huber privileges for work; may earn good time;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

AS TO COUNT 1 ONLY:
*  Serve 30 hours of community service.
